## Description {#details}

Tagged union holding either a T or a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a>.

This class parallels <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/erroror">ErrorOr</a>, but replaces error&#95;code with <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a>. Since <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> cannot be copied, this class replaces <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/targetparser/riscvisainfo-cpp/#ad73113c3c3a7bfb64703238645f6fc1e">getError()</a> with <a href="#a94789df4ebd03dc008e8adebaa66ac1f">takeError()</a>. It also adds an bool <a href="#a6fd0eefc5601ec69856713af5e06f270">errorIsA&lt;ErrT&gt;()</a> method for testing the error class type.

Example usage of &#39;Expected&lt;T&gt;&#39; as a function return type:


<ProgramListing extension="cpp">

<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="#a815f6718ecaf8321aab0587f5e62d048">Expected&lt;int&gt;</a> myDivide(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">int</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#a2e38c85003a042421cde1647632d0b72">A</a>, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">int</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#ae76959fe811ba090de4cba69ac00f1da">B</a>) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#ae76959fe811ba090de4cba69ac00f1da">B</a> == 0) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// return an Error</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a4d2fd926089a58d482fb67a362e11bad">createStringError</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a2b43c21951d0948b34bcf7019949032d">inconvertibleErrorCode</a>(),</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">                             </span><span class="doxyHighlightStringLiteral">&quot;B must not be zero!&quot;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// return an integer</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#a2e38c85003a042421cde1647632d0b72">A</a> / <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#ae76959fe811ba090de4cba69ac00f1da">B</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;</span></CodeLine>

</ProgramListing>


Checking the results of to a function returning &#39;Expected&lt;T&gt;&#39;: 
<ProgramListing extension="cpp">

<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#abb2b3a60ccc38a28239e19a1646e0c8a">E</a> = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/ms-demangle/#afb795990ffc0cb7321e7d1eacc246324a8eea62084ca7e541d918e823422bd82e">Result</a>.takeError()) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We must consume the error. Typically one of:</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - return the error to our caller</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - toString(), when logging</span></CodeLine>
